{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolP","text":"InitableProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When in “Low Power” mode, it is recommended that applications:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disable automatic downloads;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reduce the rate of refresh from online sources such as calendar or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"email synchronisation;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reduce the use of expensive visual effects."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also likely that OS components providing services to applications will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lower their own background activity, for the sake of the system."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are a variety of tools that exist for power consumption analysis, but those"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"usually depend on the OS and hardware used. On Linux, one could use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"upower"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"monitor the battery discharge rate, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"powertop"},{"type":"text","text":" to check on the background activity"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or activity at all), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sysprof"},{"type":"text","text":" to inspect CPU usage, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"intel_gpu_time"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"profile GPU usage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t forget to disconnect the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal, and unref the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" itself when exiting."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/